    "created_at": "2016-01-13T18:23:06Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-01-13T18:26:05Z",
    "body": "This is still not fixed yet. While we do hack around the issue by assigning loop\u2019s destination with the \u201creturn\u201d value of its body (i.e. unit, on every iteration), there\u2019s cases where loop\u2019s \u201creturn\u201d value is not a unit. Namely, `let x: T = loop {}` is valid \u2200T, but its body is required to have type of `()` nevertheless.\n\nAs commented https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/30636#issuecomment-168763575 by niko, we might want some sort of non-terminating kind for rvalues.\n",
